posts.name: Chris Gerth
posts.cooked:
Do not loose hope! The world, including your robot, and your current code error, is intelligible!

An unexpected error has occurred. When your robot code hits an unexpected error, you will see this message show up in some console output (Driver Station or RioLog). You’ll probably also notice you...

Specifically, you need to be looking in rioLog in vsCode, or in the larger console window of the driver station:

image 1792×350 91 KB

image 1792×350 91 KB

Read the instructions, find your error, do some thinking, and come back if you have questions or get stuck!

posts.name: Chris Gerth
posts.cooked:
Ok and one more check - be sure everything is displayed: image 940×778 196 KB

image 940×778 196 KB

image 940×778 196 KB

Hit the “Reset” button on the roboRIO and look at any new messages printed.

Confirming - nothing that looks like Robot Code Starting or An unexpected error has occurred. ?

Again be ready to think like a scientist. Asserting “nope those aren’t there” leads down one path of investigation, “yup they’er there” leads down another. Run experiments, make sure the experiments are reproducible, make conclusions, then design and run the next experiment.
